<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,1185]" pageId="6" pageNumber="563">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,538,151,176]" pageId="6" pageNumber="563">Coloration and morphology.</emphasis>
Ground colour pale brownish marked with brown, fuscous (
<figureCitation box="[1217,1341,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1950,1972]" captionTargetBox="[178,1429,1280,1909]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,1237,1929]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 5. Polyamia (Polyamia) choromorica sp. n. A–B: habitus, dorsal view; C: habitus, lateral view; D: face; E: the end of female abdomen, ventral view. A: male; B–E: female." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1458051/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="563">Fig. 5A–C</figureCitation>
). Crown white with brown, fuscous marks. Pronotum with small paired fuscous spots anteriorly and six longitudinal brown stripes. Mesonotum and scutellum with fuscous marks (
<figureCitation box="[792,918,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1950,1972]" captionTargetBox="[178,1429,1280,1909]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,1237,1929]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 5. Polyamia (Polyamia) choromorica sp. n. A–B: habitus, dorsal view; C: habitus, lateral view; D: face; E: the end of female abdomen, ventral view. A: male; B–E: female." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1458051/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="563">Fig. 5A–B</figureCitation>
). Face mostly dark brown, with paired white arcs (
<figureCitation box="[215,308,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1950,1972]" captionTargetBox="[178,1429,1280,1909]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,1237,1929]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 5. Polyamia (Polyamia) choromorica sp. n. A–B: habitus, dorsal view; C: habitus, lateral view; D: face; E: the end of female abdomen, ventral view. A: male; B–E: female." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1458051/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="563">Fig. 5D</figureCitation>
). Forewing pale brownish, veins white, cell borders dark brown (
<figureCitation box="[1074,1201,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1950,1972]" captionTargetBox="[178,1429,1280,1909]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,1237,1929]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 5. Polyamia (Polyamia) choromorica sp. n. A–B: habitus, dorsal view; C: habitus, lateral view; D: face; E: the end of female abdomen, ventral view. A: male; B–E: female." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1458051/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="563">Fig. 5A–C</figureCitation>
). Mesosternum dark brown. Femora and tibiae with fuscous marks (
<figureCitation box="[679,802,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1950,1972]" captionTargetBox="[178,1429,1280,1909]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,1237,1929]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 5. Polyamia (Polyamia) choromorica sp. n. A–B: habitus, dorsal view; C: habitus, lateral view; D: face; E: the end of female abdomen, ventral view. A: male; B–E: female." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1458051/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="563">Fig. 5C–D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,1185]" pageId="6" pageNumber="563">
Head wider than pronotum, anterior margin distinctly angulate in dorsal view. Crown longer than distance between eyes (
<figureCitation box="[315,439,367,392]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1950,1972]" captionTargetBox="[178,1429,1280,1909]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,1237,1929]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 5. Polyamia (Polyamia) choromorica sp. n. A–B: habitus, dorsal view; C: habitus, lateral view; D: face; E: the end of female abdomen, ventral view. A: male; B–E: female." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1458051/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="563">Fig. 5A–B</figureCitation>
). Clypeal sulcus absent. Anteclypeus tapering to apex, extending beyond normal curve of genae. Lorum semicircular, narrower than anteclypeus, well separated from lateral margin of face (
<figureCitation box="[1328,1423,404,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1950,1972]" captionTargetBox="[178,1429,1280,1909]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,1237,1929]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 5. Polyamia (Polyamia) choromorica sp. n. A–B: habitus, dorsal view; C: habitus, lateral view; D: face; E: the end of female abdomen, ventral view. A: male; B–E: female." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1458051/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="563">Fig. 5D</figureCitation>
). Pronotum slightly longer than vertex or nearly as long as vertex (
<figureCitation box="[889,1014,439,464]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1950,1972]" captionTargetBox="[178,1429,1280,1909]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,1237,1929]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 5. Polyamia (Polyamia) choromorica sp. n. A–B: habitus, dorsal view; C: habitus, lateral view; D: face; E: the end of female abdomen, ventral view. A: male; B–E: female." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1458051/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="563">Fig. 5A–B</figureCitation>
). Forewing exposing apex of pygofer or not, with numerous extra crossveins, especially in clavus (
<figureCitation box="[833,957,476,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1950,1972]" captionTargetBox="[178,1429,1280,1909]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,1237,1929]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 5. Polyamia (Polyamia) choromorica sp. n. A–B: habitus, dorsal view; C: habitus, lateral view; D: face; E: the end of female abdomen, ventral view. A: male; B–E: female." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1458051/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="563">Fig. 5A–C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,1185]" pageId="6" pageNumber="563">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,377,511,536]" pageId="6" pageNumber="563">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer lobe long, apex rounded, with numerous macrosetae in distal half (
<figureCitation box="[1229,1353,511,536]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1334,1356]" captionTargetBox="[182,1408,211,1305]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[150,1437,193,1312]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 6. Polyamia (Polyamia) choromorica sp. n. A: male pygofer lobe, lateral view; B: male pygofer and segments X–XI, dorsal view; C: valve, subgenital plates and styles, ventral view; D: style, dorsal view; E, F: connective and aedeagus, dorsal and lateral view, respectively." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1458053/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="563">Fig. 6A–B</figureCitation>
). Valve angulate caudally. Subgenital plate 
<date box="[563,591,548,572]" pageId="6" pageNumber="563">3x</date>
length of valve, subtriangular, lateral margin incurved, apex acute, with macrosetae arising laterally (
<figureCitation box="[487,580,583,608]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1334,1356]" captionTargetBox="[182,1408,211,1305]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[150,1437,193,1312]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 6. Polyamia (Polyamia) choromorica sp. n. A: male pygofer lobe, lateral view; B: male pygofer and segments X–XI, dorsal view; C: valve, subgenital plates and styles, ventral view; D: style, dorsal view; E, F: connective and aedeagus, dorsal and lateral view, respectively." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1458053/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="563">Fig. 6C</figureCitation>
). Style with short articulatory arm; preapical lobe rectangular; apophysis digitate, apex acute, slightly laterally curved (
<figureCitation box="[669,760,620,645]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1334,1356]" captionTargetBox="[182,1408,211,1305]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[150,1437,193,1312]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 6. Polyamia (Polyamia) choromorica sp. n. A: male pygofer lobe, lateral view; B: male pygofer and segments X–XI, dorsal view; C: valve, subgenital plates and styles, ventral view; D: style, dorsal view; E, F: connective and aedeagus, dorsal and lateral view, respectively." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1458053/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="563">Fig. 6D</figureCitation>
). Connective slightly shorter than aedeagus. Aedeagus with shaft in lateral view moderately long and slender, slightly tapered from base to apex and curved slightly dorsad, apex obliquely tapered; in ventral view slightly tapered, apex truncate with pair of small lateral projections (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1334,1356]" captionTargetBox="[182,1408,211,1305]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[150,1437,193,1312]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 6. Polyamia (Polyamia) choromorica sp. n. A: male pygofer lobe, lateral view; B: male pygofer and segments X–XI, dorsal view; C: valve, subgenital plates and styles, ventral view; D: style, dorsal view; E, F: connective and aedeagus, dorsal and lateral view, respectively." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1458053/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="563">Fig. 6E–F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,1185]" box="[199,1233,764,789]" pageId="6" pageNumber="563">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,293,764,789]" pageId="6" pageNumber="563">Female.</emphasis>
Sternite VII with posterior margin undulate, without posteriolateral lobes (
<figureCitation box="[1133,1220,764,789]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1950,1972]" captionTargetBox="[178,1429,1280,1909]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,1237,1929]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 5. Polyamia (Polyamia) choromorica sp. n. A–B: habitus, dorsal view; C: habitus, lateral view; D: face; E: the end of female abdomen, ventral view. A: male; B–E: female." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1458051/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="563">Fig. 5E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
